   antecedents of reference price and has assessed their effects through
   experimentation. Others have calibrated a variety of reference price
   models on panel data and reported the effects on brand choice and other
   purchase decisions. In this article, the authors review the published
   literature on reference price in both the behavioral and modeling
   streams. They offer an integrative framework to review prior research on
   (1) the formation of reference price, (2) retrieval and use of reference
