   activities that were designed to promote interactions among marketing
   academics and practitioners; the goal was to stimulate dialogue and new
   research on CRM. I found the proposal attractive because CRM is a
   broad-based topic that interests many marketers. After extensive
   discussion, the American Marketing Association (AMA) and the Teradata
   Center formally agreed to cosponsor the special section. Subsequently,
   there was a conference on Relationship Marketing and Customer
   Relationship Management (cochaired by Michael Ehret, Wesley Johnston,
