   simultaneous release of movies in theaters and on rental home video
   generates maximum revenues for movie studios in the United States but
   has devastating effects on other players, such as theater chains. The
   authors discuss different scenarios and their implications for movie
   studios and other industry players, and barriers for the implementation
   of the revenue-maximizing distribution models are critically reflected.
