AB This article integrates social network and exchange theory to develop a
   model of customer value based on three relational drivers: relationship
   quality (the caliber of relational ties), contact density (the number of
   relational ties), and contact authority (the decision-making capability
   of relational contacts). The results suggest that the value generated
   from interfirm relationships derives not only from the quality of
