   salespeople adopting the customer-focused sales campaign coordinated
   their sales calls with the objective of selling all the products that a
   customer was predicted to purchase only at the time the customer was
   expected to purchase. The authors compare this strategy with the current
   practice in the organization in which salespeople for each product
   category independently contacted the customers who were expected to
